Source: provsql
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), libboost-dev, libboost-serialization-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/PierreSenellart/provsql

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-provsql
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-provsql
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Semiring provenance and uncertainty management for PostgreSQL
  ProvSQL adds provenance and uncertainty management to PostgreSQL.
  It can evaluate probabilities, Shapley values, and other semiring-based
  provenance queries.
  The extension must be added to shared_preload_libraries before
  CREATE EXTENSION provsql CASCADE.
  It requires the uuid-ossp extension, included in most distribution's
  postgresql-contrib package.
